'''Sverre Krogh''' (16 August 1921 <U+2013> 6 June 2006) was a Norwegian farmer, organizational leader and politician for the [[Centre Party (Norway)|Centre Party]].

He spent his career as a farmer at Mellem-Kroer farm, [[<U+00C5>s]]. He inherited the farm from his father in 1958, and passed it on to his son in 1989.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sverre Krogh 70 <U+00E5>r 16. august|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=26 July 1991|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He was elected to the [[municipal council (Norway)|municipal council]] in <U+00C5>s in 1947, and was a council member for 28 years.<ref name=obit1>{{cite news|title=Sverre Krogh til minne|work=Nationen|first=Ellen|last=Syrstad|coauthors=Thirud, Kjell; Ellingsberg, Arne|date=26 June 2006|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He spent the years 1956 to 1975 as mayor.<ref name=ntb>{{cite news|title=Sverre Krogh 80 <U+00E5>r 16. august|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=27 July 2001|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He was also a member of [[Akershus]] [[county council (Norway)|county council]] from 1956 to 1987, twelve of these as deputy county mayor (''fylkesvaraordf<U+00F8>rer'').<ref name=obit2>{{cite news|title=Sverre Krogh|work=Aftenposten|first=Ellen|last=Syrstad|coauthors=Thirud, Kjell; Ellingsberg, Arne|date=13 June 2006|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He served as a deputy member of the [[Parliament of Norway]] during the terms 1969<U+2013>1973, 1973<U+2013>1977, and 1985<U+2013>1989.<ref>{{stortingetbio|SVKR}}</ref>

In 1972 Krogh became a member of the board of the new organization [[Norwegian Association of Local and Regional Authorities]]. From 1976 to 1984 he chaired this organization.<ref name=obit3>{{cite news|title=Sverre Krogh|work=Aftenposten|first=Halvdan|last=Skard|authorlink=Halvdan Skard|date=19 June 2006|language=Norwegian}}</ref> In 1984 he was replaced by [[Jakob Eng]], who received decisive support from the [[Conservative Party of Norway|Conservative]] and [[Christian Democratic Party of Norway|Christian Democratic]] parties&mdash;at the time coalition partners with the Centre Party in [[Willoch's Second Cabinet]].<ref name=ntb>{{cite news|title=SP-ja til AP-leder i KS intet d<U+00F8>dskyss til KrF|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=19 May 1992|language=Norwegian}}</ref> Krogh represented Norway in the [[European Conference of Local Authorities]] between 1972 and 1984, and in the [[International Union of Local Authorities]] (IULA) between 1972 and 1987. From 1972 to 1984 he was also a board member of the International Union of Local Authorities.<ref name=obit2/> He was also a member of public bodies such as ''Hovedkomiteen for reformer i lokalforvaltningen'' from 1972 to 1985.<ref name=ntb/>

In 1988 he was decorated with [[HM The King's Medal of Merit]].<ref name=ntb/> He was also an honorary member of his political party. He died in June 2006, not long before his 85th birthday.<ref name=obit1/>

